  m_text: '7. Physical interaction (2)


    In order to control how an object reacts
    to impacts, we also need a Physics Material. You can create one in Project view,
    by right click > Create >  Physics Material. You may edit its properties from
    the Inspector. The material is applied by assigning it to the "Material" attribute
    of a collider.


    EXERCISE 2: Add a Rigidbody component on the football. Set
    its linear damping to 1.0. Create/assign a suitable PhysicsMaterial with bounciness
    = 0.6, dynamic friction = 0.8, static friction = 0.6, maximum friction combine,
    and average bounce combine. Interact with the ball using your character.'
