  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "8. Physical interaction (3)\n\nEXERCISE 3: Create a script for the Football
    that implements the following logic.\n1. The ball can only be kicked if the player
    is \"close\"\n2. The ball is kicked when the left mouse button is released, with
    a force proportional to the time the left mouse button has been pressed\n3. The
    direction of the force applied to the ball is the vector joining the center of
    the player and the center of the ball\n\nHINTS: \n1. The player has gameObject.tag
    == \"Player\"\n2. Input.GetMouseButton(int button) tells you if \"button\" is
    being pressed. The left mouse button is identified by Mouse0 in KeyCode."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
