  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '6. Physical interaction (1)


    Colliders are not enough to achieve
    physics-based behaviour: we also need Rigidbodies. When an object has a Rigidbody
    component, Unity will include in the physics engine computations.


    IMPORTANT:
    in your scripts, code that manipulates Rigidbody properties (e.g. adding forces)
    should be implemented inside FixedUpdate() rather than Update(): this is because
    the update time of the physics engine (Time.fixedDeltaTime) is not necessarily
    the same as the regular frame update (Time.deltaTime).


'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
