  m_text: '11. Colliders in Unity code (1)


    But how do we interact with colliders
    in scripts? Well, as usual, Collider classes expose methods you may override.
    These events only happen if one of the involved objects has a non-kinematic Rigidbody
    attached. Plus, they are also sent to disabled MonoBehaviours, to allow for enabling
    in response to a collision occurring.

'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
