      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "14. Trigger colliders (1)\n\nWe can obtain a trigger collider by checking
    the \"Is Trigger\" attribute of a collider. This type of collider do not activate
    collisions, and they do not influence physical simulations. \n\nAs a consequence,
    trigger colliders are used somewhat differently than regular ones. \n1. Their
    behaviour is usually entirely user-specified, via custom code\n2. They are frequently
    attached to invisible or empty objects, as we generally only want them to specify
    abstract \"regions\" that trigger some game logic when they are stepped into."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
