  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "3. Solid objects (2)\n\nTry to move through the sphere now: your character
    will be prevented from doing that by the new Collider we created. This happens,
    of course, because your character **also** has a collider attached to it. \n\nIn
    Scene mode, select the ball again in the Hierarchy: you will notice a new gizmo
    on the object, some sort of green cage-looking structure. That \"cage\" defines
    the boundary of the collider, and it can usually be edited. \n\nWhen you add
    a collider on an object with a MeshFilter component, its size and position are
    usually computed to achieve the best overlap with the geometry.\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
