  m_text: '1. Introduction


    In the first part of this lab, we will discuss collisions.


    In
    general, collisions may be used in Unity to:

    1. Define solid objects

    2.
    Simulate physical interaction

    3. Detect position-based events


    We will
    cover these three use cases one by one.'
