      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '9. Collision detection (1)


    Unity offers various algorithms to detect
    rigidbody collisions in the physics engine. These can be selected on a per-object
    basis via the Rigidbody.collisionDetection attribute.


    "Discrete" is the
    default and the fastest one. It''s usually good enough but may miss collisions
    of fast-moving objects.


    "ContinuousDynamic" should be applied to fast moving
    objects.


    "Continuous" should be applied to objects that receive collisions
    from fast moving objects.


    "ContinuousSpeculative" is a slightly more efficient
    approximation which works for both static and moving objects.'
