  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "4. Solid objects (3)\n\nOther type of \"primitive\" colliders supported
    by Unity are BoxColliders and CapsuleColliders. Add these to the objects on the
    left and try editing them (either by changing their parameters manually or using
    the editing handles on the cage).\n\nNow, a spontaneous question you may have
    is \"what about more complex objects? not everything in a game is a cube, a sphere
    or a capsule\". \nFor colliders, the keyword is \"compositionality\". Very often,
    3D objects are made by artist in a compositional manner, which allows us to employ
    simple colliders applied to each individual part. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
