  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '5. Solid objects (3)


    EXERCISE 1: add colliders to the character
    on the right. He''s in the Hierarchy as Objects > Human. Locate his body parts
    in his children GameObjects and add suitable colliders to each.


    In cases
    where we want a very accurate collider, we can always resort to MeshColliders,
    which are derived from the object geometry. However, computing their intersections
    is costly, so you want to use them sparingly, and only for static objects. Behind
    this slide, you may find a comparison of physical interactions between a composition
    of simple colliders and a mesh collider. Get close to the fountains and press
    P to start the example.'
